name: places/ChIJWzgEFwAb2jERME_t9kLeFRg/reviews/ChZDSUhNMG9nS0VNT1huUFA3LXYtT0lREAE
text:
{'text': "Cathay Cineplex at Clementi 321 is one of the best remaining cinemas under the Cathay brand in Singapore. While it's relatively small, the cinema offers great screens, comfortable seating, and clear sound quality, making for a pleasant and reliable movie-watching experience. It's conveniently located near Clementi MRT, making it easily accessible for West-side residents.

The transition from WE Cinemas to Cathay brought new energy to the space, but it's also a little bittersweet, as we see one of Singapore’s iconic cinema chains slowly losing ground. It’s a reminder of how quickly the entertainment landscape is changing.

One minor inconvenience is that the escalator at 321 Clementi is currently down, which may be challenging for those with mobility concerns. Still, the cinema itself remains a favorite among locals looking for a cozy, quality theatre experience.
Clementi 321 remains a great spot for catching the latest movies without the crowds of larger malls.", 'languageCode': 'en'}

text: {'text': 'The Malay girl staff’s attitude is very bad as she pretends to avoid work or serving customers at the counter and when I asked her if she could help my elderly father and myself to the lift passage way, she pointed us to the faulty escalator which made us both breathless afterwards…. name: places/ChIJWzgEFwAb2jERME_t9kLeFRg/reviews/ChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUNfam9mRTJnRRAB
text: {'text': 'Was very pleased with the service by Yi Lin, who helped me with my tickets and food. She even pointed me to an existing promotion that helped me save a few dollars on my popcorn combo. I really appreciated that.\n\nHowever, I was quite annoyed by the way the seats are connected to each other. Every time another patron would shift in their seat or raise/put down the armrest, the entire row would shake. It made for quite a distracting experience during the show.', 'languageCode': 'en'}
